-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu May 08, 2014 06:09AM EDT
-- None



May 8 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Thursday:

** Australia's Envestra Ltd <ENV.AX> said on Thursday it has received a conditional takeover offer from Hong Kong's Cheung Kong Group <0001.HK>, valuing the natural gas distributor at A$2.37 billion ($2.21 billion) and trumping an earlier bid from Australian Pipeline Ltd (APA). [ID:nL3N0NU3CL]  ** British utility Centrica Plc <CNA.L> announced on Thursday it was selling a 40 percent stake in its Canadian natural gas business to joint venture partner Qatar Petroleum International for around $200 million. [ID:nL6N0NU1KX]  ** Suntory Holdings Ltd [SUNTH.UL] aims to raise about 800 billion yen ($7.87 billion) in debt to finance its purchase of U.S. spirits company Beam Inc, Japan's third-biggest outbound deal ever, people familiar with the situation said. [ID:nT9N0N309Z]  ** Alibaba Group Holding Ltd <IPO-ALIB.N> has struck one of its largest deals with a U.S. e-commerce company, agreeing to help Amazon.com <AMZN.O> rival ShopRunner expand into China. [ID:nL2N0NT2A5]  ** CVC Capital Partners has agreed to buy South Korea's KFC franchise from a subsidiary of Doosan Co Ltd <000150.KS> for 100 billion won ($98 million), Doosan said on Thursday. [ID:nL3N0NU3VP]  ** U.S. private equity firm Ripplewood has acquired a 10 percent stake in Egypt's third-largest listed property developer SODIC <OCDI.CA> for 217.17 million Egyptian pounds ($30.89 million), a source informed about the deal told Reuters on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0NU2A2] ** TriOil Resources, the Canadian upstream unit of Poland's top oil refiner, PKN Orlen <PKN.WA>, bought its local rival Birchill Exploration, making good on the promise to buy oil production assets to increase profitability, PKN said on Thursday. [ID:nW8N0NH008]  ** Google Ventures <GOOG.O> led a $130 million investment in oncology-data company Flatiron Health, Flatiron said on Wednesday. [ID:nL2N0NU039]  ** Private equity firms, including Corsair Capital, were approached to take part in a 400 million pound ($678.62 million)rescue fundraising for the struggling Co-op Bank, according to Sky News and a source familiar with the matter. [ID:nL6N0NT74A]  ** Private equity firm GI Partners is in exclusive talks to acquire Peak 10 Inc in a deal that could value the information technology infrastructure company at between $800 million and $900 million, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0NT2LX]  ** DirecTV <DTV.O> is working with advisers including Goldman Sachs Group <GS.N> to evaluate a possible combination with AT&T Inc <T.N>, following a recent takeover approach from the mobile services provider, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0NT2CU]  ** General Electric Co <GE.N> has agreed to sell its Wayne fuel dispenser business to private investment firm Riverstone Holdings LLC, the U.S. conglomerate said on Wednesday. [ID:nL2N0NT2AV]